    {
      "_id": "23d839a7b063dc4c",
      "name": "Pre-Combat Aggression",
      "sort": 4,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-809d-8745-fedf53b1466a\">The moment a Combat Encounter begins is not always a matter of strict timing. The GM may determine that a PC’s action (such as drawing steel, loosing an arrow, or invoking a spell) triggers the clash, allowing them to carry out that action before Initiative is rolled. However, if the enemy is already on high alert or poised for battle, the GM may rule that combat begins before the action can be completed, requiring the character to take their aggressive move on their first turn instead.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
      "title": {
        "level": 3,
        "show": true
      },
      "type": "text",
