    {
      "_id": "be23eff1415b58c0",
      "name": "Duration in Rounds",
      "sort": 18,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80bd-b786-e6f62a358ce1\">The duration of some effects are measured in Rounds. The duration of these effects are measured from the start of the creature’s Turn they are produced until the start of that same creature’s Turn the specified number of Rounds later.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80ac-b468-c1474ed93b6a\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\">Example: If an effect with a duration of 1 Round was produced on a creature’s Turn, that effect would persist until the start of that creature’s next Turn. If the effect lasted 2 Rounds, then the effect would persist until the start of that creature’s Turn 2 Rounds later.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80a9-8896-e620370c0d97\" class=\"block-color-purple_background\">DC Tip: Referring to the first Round of Combat means the first 12 seconds, where each creature will have 1 turn. But if a PC uses an ability that lasts for 1 Round, that effect still lasts 12 seconds (which means each creature will have 1 Turn since the use of that ability), and it would last until the start of that creature’s next Turn.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
